commit.message:
Send UTF8 command to POP3 server (ignore the response), because some servers
don't like UTF-8 without it.
Replace obsolete macros AC_HELP_STRING and AC_TRY_LINK, from Aaron Ji.
Fix use-after-free, GitHub issue 126.

Fix bugs in PCRE2 code - don't walk off the end of the match list if NOMATCH is
returned, and don't stop on empty matches. From Thomas Hurst.
Remove double copy.
Use PCRE2, from ben at bvnf dot space; GitHub issue 111.
Do not kill children when we already requested they exit, from M Vefa Bicakci.
Allow using a specific machine username from .netrc, from Denis Carikli.
Base64 encode PLAIN.
No extra trailing \0.
Allow empty writes.
Fix token order.
Support for LMTP, from someone who wishes to remain anonymous.
Support for XOAUTH2 and PLAIN, with help from Kenny MacDermid.
Document/example of folder tag, from hspaij in GitHub issue 98.
Do not ignore child process failure, from Kyle George. GitHub issue 95.
Remove/change some unused variables, from Martin Vahlensieck.
Add some missing tags, from Martin Vahlensieck.

Add support for OAUTHBEARER (OAuth 2.0 bearer tokens, as documented by RFC
7628) for IMAP, from Leonardo Taccari.
Fix with old OpenSSL functions, from Rosen Penev.

IMAP delivery - fix a bug in CRLF handling, and handle problems with Apple's
IMAP server (similar to changes made earlier for fetching).

Patch from Willemijn Coene in GitHub issue 79.
Don't log NULL, GitHub issue 78.

Apple's IMAP implementation is extremely crap and just disconnects if fdm tries
to send a string continuation, so try a quoted string instead if the user and
password for LOGIN and folder name for SELECT don't include " or { or }.

I initially tried implementing AUTH=PLAIN but their implementation of it is
also broken (despite the capability being listed).
Ignore NULL user.
Allow empty MAIL FROM in SMTP, from Volker Klasen.
Fix a warning, from Alexander Huemer.
Update user before replacing tags when parsing, GitHub issue 70.
Don't log NULL FQDN, reported by Marc Espie.
